triples.evidence: This property is the basis for positron emission tomography, or PET.
By detecting pairs of gamma photons and knowing they must lie along the same line, we can reconstruct the location where the positron annihilation occurred.

concepts.term: this annihilation produces two gamma photons, each with an energy of 511 kilo-electronvolts

evidence: When they meet, they annihilate each other. This annihilation produces two gamma photons, each with an energy of 511 kilo-electronvolts. These photons travel in opposite directions, almost exactly 180 degrees apart.
